At least 41 flights were affected by jet fuel shortages at OR Tambo International Airport last week. Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula says 32 of those flights were domestic, eight international and one was regional. eNCA's Heidi Giokos has more details. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - At least 41 flights were affected by last week's jet fuel shortages at OR Tambo International Airport. Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula says the incident was a result of a technical glitch in the storage facility. READ: Flights delayed at OR Tambo airport Mbalula says 32 of the affected flights were domestic, 8 international, and 1 regional. He conducted an oversight visit at the airport on Monday. Watch the video above for more details.